<item>
            <title>[HBASE-9805] shell scripts override environment value of HBASE_OPTS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9805</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7091&quot; title=&quot;support custom GC options in hbase-env.sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7091&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7091&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it&apos;s not longer possible to specify overrides to &lt;tt&gt;HBASE_OPTS&lt;/tt&gt; on the command line. That makes it difficult to do things like enabling assertions while running a specific test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reading through that ticket&apos;s description, this may be by design.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
